  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Will I get disability benefits for govt jobs after a bike accident?",
  "response": "Whether you will receive disability benefits for a government job after a bike accident depends on several factors, including the specific policies of the government agency you work for, the nature and severity of your injuries, and the applicable disability laws.\n\n1. **Type of Disability**: If your injuries prevent you from performing your job or any other suitable work, you may qualify for disability benefits. These can include short-term disability, long-term disability, and workers' compensation benefits if the accident occurred while performing work-related duties.\n\n2. **Government Policies**: Different government agencies have their own procedures for disability claims. You should reach out to your HR department or the appropriate benefits office within your agency for information on the specific requirements and processes.\n\n3. **Documentation**: You'll likely need medical documentation to support your claim, detailing the nature of your injuries and how they affect your ability to work.\n\n4. **Legal Framework**: You may also need to consider any relevant laws, such as the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), which provides protections for individuals with disabilities in the workplace, including public sector jobs.\n\n5. **Consulting Professionals**: It may be beneficial to consult with a disability attorney or a qualified professional who can provide specific guidance based on your circumstances.\n\nMake sure to act quickly, as there may be deadlines for filing claims for disability benefits.",
